<h1>EsqSites123.com's Privacy Policy </h1>

<h3>What This Privacy Policy Covers</h3>
<p>This policy covers how EsqSites treats personal information that EsqSites collects and receives, including information related to your past use of EsqSites products and services. Personal information is information about you that is personally identifiable like your name, address, email address, or phone number, and that is not otherwise publicly available. </p>
<p>This policy does not apply to the practices of companies that EsqSites does not own or control, or to people that EsqSites does not employ or manage.</p>

<h2>Information Collection and Use </h2>
<h3>General </h3>
<p>EsqSites collects personal information when you register with EsqSites, when you use EsqSites products or services, when you visit EsqSites pages or the pages of certain EsqSites partner. EsqSites may combine information about you that we have with information we obtain from business partners or other companies. </p>

<p>When you register we ask for information such as your name, email address, birth date, gender, zip code, address, and Social Security number. Once you register with EsqSites and sign in to our services, you are not anonymous to us. </p>

<p>EsqSites automatically receives and records information on our server logs from your browser, including your IP address, EsqSites cookie information, and the page you request. </p>
<p>EsqSites uses information for the following general purposes: to improve our services, contact you, conduct research, and provide anonymous reporting for internal and external clients. </p>

<h3>Information Sharing and Disclosure </h3>
<p>EsqSites does not rent, sell, or share personal information about you with other people or nonaffiliated companies except to provide products or services you've requested, when we have your permission, or under the following circumstances: </p>
<p>We respond to subpoenas, court orders, or legal process, or to establish or exercise our legal rights or defend against legal claims; </p>
<p>We believe it is necessary to share information in order to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person, violations of EsqSites's terms of use, or as otherwise required by law. </p>
<p>We transfer information about you if EsqSites is acquired by or merged with another company. In this event, EsqSites will notify you before information about you is transferred and becomes subject to a different privacy policy. </p>
<p>EsqSites displays targeted advertisements based on personal information.</p>
<p>EsqSites works with vendors, partners, advertisers, and other service providers in different industries and categories of business. For more information regarding providers of products or services that you've requested please read our detailed reference links. </p>

<h3>Cookies </h3>
<p>EsqSites may set and access EsqSites cookies on your computer. </p>
<p>EsqSites lets other companies that show advertisements on some of our pages set and access their cookies on your computer. Other companies' use of their cookies is subject to their own privacy policies, not this one. Advertisers or other companies do not have access to EsqSites's cookies. </p>
<p>EsqSites uses web beacons to access EsqSites cookies inside and outside our network of web sites and in connection with EsqSites products and services. </p>

<h2>Your Ability to Edit and Delete Your Account Information and Preferences </h2>
<h3>General </h3>
<p>You can edit your EsqSites Account Information at any time. </p>
<p>We reserve the right to send you certain communications relating to the EsqSites service, such as service announcements, administrative messages and the EsqSites Newsletter, that are considered part of your EsqSites account, without offering you the opportunity to opt-out of receiving them. </p>
<p>You can delete your EsqSites account by visiting our the Client Login portion of our site.</p>

<h3>Confidentiality and Security </h3>
<p>We limit access to personal information about you to employees who we believe reasonably need to come into contact with that information to provide products or services to you or in order to do their jobs. </p>
<p>We have physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards that comply with federal regulations to protect personal information about you. </p>

<h3>Changes to this Privacy Policy </h3>
<p>EsqSites may update this policy. We will notify you about significant changes in the way we treat personal information by sending a notice to the primary email address specified in your EsqSites account or by placing a prominent notice on our site. </p>